Method Detail

epoch

public void epoch(Population<D> population)
Evolves the given Population via mutation or crossover, reevaluates it, and performs any other processing.

Evolution proceeds as follows:

  1. Species are removed from the population as determined by the NEATSurvivalFilter; their genomes will not reproduce
  2. Genomes are marked for death by the NEATSurvivalFilter, but are still made available for reproduction
  3. A number of children are produced equal to the number genomes dying this generation, so that the population size remains constant
  4. A round of speciation occurs to place the new genomes into the appropriate species (or new species as need be)
  5. The population is evaluated
  6. A round of speciation occurs if the number of species is outside the bounds specified in NEATEvolutionFieldMap
  7. The population's statistics are updated and a report is made

Specified by:
epoch in interface EvolutionStrategy<D,T>
Overrides:
epoch in class AbstractEvolutionStrategy<D,T>
Parameters:
population - the collection of genomes to evolve for one generation

(com.xtructure.xevolution.genetics.Population)

initialize

public void initialize(Population<D> population)
Performs an initial evaluation and any pre-evolution processing on the given Population. This method is intended to be called once, before any evolution takes place.

Initialization proceeds as follows:

  1. The population is evaluated
  2. A round of speciation occurs to determine the population's initial species assignment
  3. The population's statistics are updated and a report is made

Specified by:
initialize in interface EvolutionStrategy<D,T>
Overrides:
initialize in class AbstractEvolutionStrategy<D,T>
